headline.main: Threat to Egypt; Situation Held Critical but Not Forlorn -- British May Stand East of El Daba

lead_paragraph: The armored spearhead of Axis tanks had roared to within 100 miles of Alexandria last night and there were no signs that the impetus of the enemy drive had yet been checked.
abstract: H W Baldwin on Axis threat to Egypt
